OL,3,CAfcon final result overturned and
OL,4,CMorocco named tournament winners
OL,6,FIn the January 18 final in Rabat,
OL,7,FSenegal left the field in protest
OL,8,Fduring stoppage time for 15 minutes,
OL,9,Fand fans tried to storm the field when
OL,10,FMorocco was awarded a penalty.
OL,12,FWhen play resumed, Morocco forward
OL,13,FBrahim Diaz's penalty was saved, and
OL,14,FSenegal scored the only goal in extra
OL,15,Ftime.
OL,17,FAt an initial disciplinary hearing,
OL,18,FCAF imposed fines of more than $1
OL,19,Fmillion and bans for Senegal and
OL,20,FMorocco players and officials, but the
OL,21,Fresult was left untouched.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/3
